#12300
The Southern Gate~
   This is the southern gate of Garnet, a dwarven settlement.  Solamnia granted
the dwarves of Thorbardin mining and settlement rights to this land for their
aid against the ogres which had been terrorizing Solamnic lands.  The
settlement was named for its location of course, being in the Garnet mountains.
The dwarves have not had time to entrench themselves quite yet, and so this
gate is little more than a break in a six foot tall, stone wall which surrounds
the majority of the settlement itself.  It is wide enough to allow the passage
of wagons, though the dwarves keep an eye on anyone coming through the gate.  
