The Garnet Stables~
   As you enter the stable, the smell of hay assaults your nostrils instantly.
Beneath this smell is the dung heap out back.  A dwarven child stands ready to
take the reins of your mount as you enter, his small, dirty hands outstretched
for his required fee.  Horses and other beasts of burden neigh and whicker in
their stalls, as they casually munch the hay provided for them.  In the corner,
you notice a brush and a pail, obviously for brushing the animals and for
bringing them fresh water.  By the door you entered, a stack of saddles lay
waiting for their owners, each one marked by a ticket, to remind the young
stablehand which animal the saddle goes to.    
